  "informal_statement": "For every natural number n, n is strictly less than 2 raised to the n (equivalently, 2^n > n).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Induction on n. Base case n = 0: 0 < 2^0 = 1 by norm_num. Successor case: given ih : n < 2^n, rewrite 2^(n+1) via pow_succ to 2^n * 2, then nlinarith closes n + 1 < 2^n * 2 from ih. A direct nlinarith attempt on the un-rewritten goal fails first (see the paired negative example negative.induction.pow_succ_atom_nlinarith_failure.v1): nlinarith cannot relate the opaque atoms 2^(n+1) and 2^n without the pow_succ bridge.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem two_pow_gt_self (n : ℕ) : n < 2 ^ n",
